# Rust build output
/target/
**/*.rs.bk
# Cargo.lock IS committed — this is a binary-producing workspace, so
# the lock file pins every dep to a reproducible version. Library
# crates omit it; binary crates commit it.

# Tauri build output
/app/src-tauri/target/
/app/node_modules/

# NOTE: `app/dist/` is NOT ignored. In a standard Tauri layout where
# the frontend has a build step (Vite, Svelte, React), `dist/` is
# the build artefact and gets ignored. This project ships vanilla
# HTML/CSS/JS from `app/dist/` directly — Tauri's `frontendDist`
# serves those files verbatim, no build step — so `app/dist/` IS
# the source tree and must be tracked.

# Editor / OS
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Large binary test fixtures are committed when small (<2 MB). Larger
# ones go through Git LFS — uncomment if we adopt LFS later.
# *.mp4
# *.mov
